    "body": "### Problem\n\nSee below\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\n2. Source the following Lua file\n```lua\n_G.count = 0\nlocal timer = vim.uv.new_timer()\ntimer:start(10, 10, function() end)\nvim.wait(1000, function() _G.count = _G.count + 1 end, 200)\ntimer:close()\nprint(_G.count)\n```\n3. The value of `_G.count` is over 100.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe value of `_G.count` should be much smaller.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2278+g88dc44260f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.45.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
